  "explanation": "The defendant, serving in a position of trust as an accountant, abused that position to embezzle $25,000. However, mitigating circumstances are significant: the defendant has no prior criminal record and has demonstrated remorse and a commitment to correction by partially paying back the embezzled funds. A brief period of incarceration of 3 months is sufficient to punish the breach of trust and deter future misconduct, while acknowledging the mitigating factors and facilitating the outstanding restitution upon release.",
  "verdict": 3
}
